      "writtenOn": "2020-08-06T05:41:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "when returning an error is easy, ie you don\u0027t need to propagate it through layers and layers of otherwise clean algorithmic functions, just return it. At call site, it\u0027d be easier to log additional details.\n\nand to remain succinct in tests, use helper to assert error:\n  run :\u003d func(...) []cls{\n    res, err :\u003d Optimize(...)\n    if err !\u003d nil {panic(err)}  \n    return res\n  }\n\n\n(I use panic in helpers instead of So(err, ShouldBeNil) to get full stack in GoConvey Web UI instead of useless line number)",
      "range": {
