        "uuid": "5e2d266f_f1a0be34",
        "filename": "cq/internal/submission/order.go",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 129,
      "author": {
        "id": 1381059
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-06T23:03:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I\u0027d bet this is where all the time is burned. If dep.Key was an index of a CL in a cls list, then this wouldn\u0027t be a problem.\n\u003e This can be pre-computed in O(E). In fact, CLs themselves can be identified by index, too.\n\nWould you mind explain more on this? Are you indicating that for actual CL struct in the future, it probably won\u0027t have attribute Key which needs to be computed over and over again (i.e. host+number)?",
      "parentUuid": "eadc02d4_6847735e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 129,
        "startChar": 14,
        "endLine": 129,
        "endChar": 37
      },
      "revId": "09627ce5dd39ae68635c84cf15c0a6cb1a6b3f8e",
