    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a9dbe2ac_aca15357",
        "filename": "cq/internal/submission/order.go",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 129,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114919
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-07T00:13:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "no. CL will have a key. I dunno how deps will look like.\n\nWhat\u0027s certain here is that in the worst case, this line will be executed O(E*V) times, which I think is where we pay major cost (but needs profiling to be sure).\nIf we precompute at the start of optimize deps for each CL based on *indexes*, then we can save O(E*V) hashing of strings.\n\nFrom big-O notation, what i\u0027m saying is that hashtable access is actually foremost computing hash of a string key, denoted HASH(key), not O(1).\nSo, right now we pay O(E*V*HASH) \u003d O(V^3*HASH). We could instead pay \n  O(E*HASH)  // replace Dep.Key with Dep.Index\n  + \n  O(E*V*1)       // this line becomes true O(1)\n\nIn your benchmarks, len(key) \u003c\u003d 3. In real life, it\u0027d be ~40-50 chars.\nIn practice, hash computation has high initial overhead, so it probably won\u0027t get 20x slow, i\u0027d say ~3x slower. You can change benchmark to generate smth like\n\"chromium-review.googlesource.com/123124\" and see if it changes things.\n\nIn any case, this isn\u0027t important right now. This CL should land as is.",
      "parentUuid": "5e2d266f_f1a0be34",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 129,
        "startChar": 14,
        "endLine": 129,
        "endChar": 37
      },
